Ad Text:
Join the change. Electrify your future!
We've been proudly Aussie since 1837, always finding new ways to innovate in energy and essential services. Now, we're moving towards a sustainable future through electrification and investing in renewable energy-and we'd like you to join us. Whether you're on-site, in the office, or somewhere in between, you'll find opportunities to grow your career here. You'll work with a team that's passionate about powering Australian lives, in a culture that values inclusivity, respect, and learning. Help us create a cleaner energy future, and we'll back you every step of the way as you build your career.

Join the change. Electrify your future.

About the role
The Data Scientist, part of the Data Science Chapter within Product & Commercial, plays a crucial role in driving AGL's profitability. They build and maintain advanced data models, analyse complex datasets, and develop predictive models to solve business problems and uncover growth opportunities.

Reporting functionally to the GM of Product & Commercial and the Data Science chapter lead, Data Scientists are embedded in cross-functional teams to support business objectives. They maintain strong ties with the Data Science Chapter for capability development, knowledge sharing, and aligning on data practices, while being accountable for upholding data standards and achieving business goals.

What you'll be doing:

Build and iterate machine learning models to tackle business challenges like customer segmentation and marketing optimization.
Enhance model performance through feature engineering, hyperparameter tuning, and ensemble methods.
Conduct experiments to test hypotheses and derive actionable insights from data.
Create compelling visualizations to effectively communicate complex insights to stakeholders.
Identify new applications for data science to generate refined insights.
Stay updated on industry trends and emerging technologies to drive innovation

About you:

Previous demonstrated experience in customer segmentation and predictive behaviour modelling.
Strong analytical skills, with experience in applying statistical techniques to solve business problems.
Proficient in developing and implementing predictive models, segmentation models, and other statistical models using tools such as R, Python, or SAS (Python preferred).
Basic SQL skills and understanding of version control systems (ie. Git repository)
Experience in using data visualization tools such as Tableau or Power BI to effectively communicate complex findings to both technical and non-technical stakeholders.
Knowledge of the energy industry, including familiarity with energy consumption patterns, regulatory frameworks, and industry-specific challenges. - preferred - not essential.

At AGL, we offer a wide range of benefits including:

Flexible working options including hybrid work.
Discounts on energy, telcos and solar plans.
Participate in Energise - our reward & recognition program.
Access 20 weeks of paid parental leave for the primary carer.
Access to an additional week of recharge leave per year.
Play an active role in our diversity & inclusion initiatives.
Novated leasing and Electric Vehicle subscriptions.
Access to study assistance, AGL's share purchase plan and insurance deals.

*Benefits may change over time and vary based on role type and location.

Inclusion at AGL
At AGL, we value diversity and welcome applicants from various backgrounds, including Aboriginal and/or Torres Strait Islander peoples, individuals with disabilities, culturally diverse individuals, and members of the LGBTQ+ community. AGL is dedicated to maintaining a diverse workforce and encourages applicants to share their lived experiences.
We offer reasonable adjustments throughout the recruitment process and respect the privacy of those who choose not to disclose. To learn more visit: www.agl.com.au/careers

AGL is proud to be a WORK180 Endorsed Employer for All Women.
Our pre-employment screening process includes a Nationally Coordinated Criminal History Check and a medical assessment if necessary.

The information provided as part of your application to AGL will be managed in accordance with the AGL Privacy Policy.

AGL does not accept agency submissions unless approval has been granted by a member of the Talent Acquisition team. Candidates submitted by an agency without approval will not be considered by AGL.

Ad Text:
Reporting to the Automation Manager, the Automation Engineer position is a subject matter expert for automation, electrical and control systems.

The focus of this role is to ensure reliability, robustness, throughput and security of new and existing equipment/systems. This is done by completing or contributing towards projects and implementing other minor modifications/changes as required. This role contributes to the overall plan towards Industry 4.0 and the integration of other business systems such as SAP with factory automation.

Additionally, this position supports the factory with day to day issues that arise involving the automation and electrical systems including PLC/SCADA and other OT software.

Day to day responsibilities include:

Project support/system design

Implement minor projects and participate as a team member for larger projects

·       Implement PLC hardware and software changes

·       Make changes to HMIs/SCADAs and other OT systems as required

·       Undertake electrical designs including cabinet layouts

·       Produce electrical drawings for modifications

·       Prepare design specifications and work packages Technicians and Contractors

·       Develop User Requirement Specifications (URS) and Qualification documents (IQ/OQ/PQ)

·       Complete commissioning and validation/qualification where required

·       Design, program and document small automation projects autonomously

·       Coordinate contractors and tradespeople to perform automation works including both software and hardware

Day to day support

Provide technical support to resolve day to day issues on the PLC network, servers and automation software

·       Support Technicians with troubleshooting issues related to automation

·       Investigate deviation incidents and implement corrective actions

·       Become subject matter expert for automation system software (Iltis, 3WS, C# applications)

·       Administer and manage applications on the factory network such as 3WS and user management on Active Directory

·       Update and upgrade automation and Windows operating systems to ensure that cyber security risks are minimised

·       Provide support to production on new equipment

Documentation

Ensure that adequate and accurate documentation is generated and stored with a high attention to detail

·       Manage and complete electrical drawing updates

·       Perform critical spares assessments

·       Ensure software backups are correctly stored in the backups repository

·       Ensure that appropriate system documentation is filed in the Engineering DMS folders

·       Ensure that safety design, validation and testing documentation is filed in the Engineering DMS folders

·       Create Isolation Procedures where required

·       Complete Change Management documentation

GxP

Ensure the principles of GxP are observed through all activities

·       Maintain an understanding of the principles of GxP

·       Ensure routine tasks are covered by approved Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs)

·       Ensure relevant changes are covered by Change Control Procedures (CCPs) with appropriate authorisation and testing


WORK RELATED REQUIREMENTS/SELECTION CRITERIA

EDUCATION/QUALIFICATIONS

Bachelor Engineering (Electrical, Mechatronics or Software)

EXPERIENCE

Experience in a manufacturing environment or as a system integrator (pharmaceutical, cosmetics, food or chemical industries would be relevant) is desirable

REQUIRED SKILLS

·       Strong fault finding and problem solving abilities

·       Ability to work effectively in a team or individually

·       High attention to detail

·       Good communication skills, both written and oral

·       Experience programming, maintaining and commissioning PLC hardware and software (Siemens, Allen-Bradley etc.)

·       Experience configuring, maintaining and commissioning SCADA/Historian/OPC software packages

·       Programming experience (.NET C#, ladder (Rockwell, Siemens))

·       Understanding of industrial Ethernet networks (VLANs, subnets)

·       Experience designing safety systems in accordance with AS/NZS 4024

·       Electrical drawing design and updating (AutoCAD or similar)

·       GAMP5 experience (desirable)

Must have PR, AU or NZ Citizenship to be eligible to apply.

Ad Text:
Full Time / 9-day fortnight / 36.00 hours per week
$111,401 - $117,924 per annum
Position Brief - Data Engineer and Developer

About the team

We're entering a new chapter for the Chief Technology Office at the City of Gold Coast as we deliver bold, future-focussed solutions. With the launch of our IT Operating Model, as well as bringing critical IT services in-house, we are transforming the way we deliver technology services — making them faster, more responsive and more aligned with the needs of our organisation and customers.

As part of this transformation, we're hiring multiple new positions. These roles are key to shaping a vibrant and forward-thinking Chief Technology Office, one that adds real value, delivers better outcomes, and works in smarter, more agile ways.

If you are equally excited about innovation, transformation and making a meaningful impact, now is the perfect time to join us.

About the role

As a Data Engineer & Developer, you will design, develop and maintain scalable data pipelines that bring together data from across the organisation into a unified, accessible and trusted data environment.

You will play a key role in ensuring data quality, reliability and performance, while enabling business intelligence, reporting and advanced analytics capabilities. Working closely with business analysts, data scientists and other technology teams, you will deliver high-quality data products that support strategic decision-making and drive measurable business value.

We’re looking for people who have:

We’re looking for motivated and technically capable data professionals who are passionate about building reliable, scalable data solutions and working collaboratively in a modern data environment.

You will bring:

A Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, Data Science, Information Technology or a related technical field
3–5 years’ experience in data engineering, business intelligence or a related technical role
Strong experience with data pipelines and workflow orchestration tools such as Apache Airflow, Databricks and/or Spark
Hands-on experience designing and working with modern data platforms and analytics environments
Microsoft Certified: Fabric Data Engineer Associate (DP-700) or equivalent practical experience and knowledge
Strong problem-solving skills, attention to detail and a collaborative mindset

Be part of shaping the Gold Coast’s future

The Gold Coast is inspired by lifestyle and driven by opportunity. We are the second largest Council in Australia.

We care about being the most flexible government organisation in Australia. We have a range of benefits to help you create the right balance:

9-day fortnight
Flexible work arrangements to suit your lifestyle, including hybrid/work from home options, flexible working hours and locations
Personal and professional development courses
Access to 350+ fitness facilities through Fitness Passport
4 free confidential counselling sessions a year for you or an immediate family member
1 free nutritionist and financial advice session per year

We pride ourselves on our shared mission of being a high-performing, customer-focused organisation which delivers value-for-money services to the community.

How to apply

To submit your application, please click apply now and complete the application form. You will be required to upload your resume and a cover letter (no more than two pages) outlining how your skills, experience and personal attributes will enable you to be successful in this role. Please note that you may also be asked to provide relevant qualifications, where applicable.

Contact Person Ashley Shannon

Contact Email ashannon@goldcoast.qld.gov.au

Closing Date 7th February 2026, 11:59pm

We’re committed to creating a diverse workplace and inclusive culture. We take pride in people who align with our high-performance principles. We believe that the diverse makeup of our workforce reflects the community we serve. We consider all qualified candidates for employment, irrespective of race, age, religion, gender identity, sexual orientation, disability, or other protected characteristics by law.

Ad Text:
Job Title: Mid-Level AI Analyst - Governance & Ethics
Location: Sydney CBD
Employment Type: Full-time / long term contract opportunity
Salary: Negotiable contract rate on offer

About the Role

We are seeking a hands-on Mid-Level AI Analyst, and this role is ideal for someone passionate about AI governance, ethics, and responsible AI frameworks, who enjoys translating complex technical risks into practical advice and solutions.
You will work across government, enterprise, and technical teams to assess AI initiatives, monitor compliance, and support the implementation of robust governance processes. This is not a policy-making role , it's analytical, advisory, and deeply hands-on, offering exposure to cutting-edge AI projects in a high-impact environment.

Key Responsibilities

Conduct AI governance and ethics assessments across projects, identifying potential risks, bias, fairness, and compliance issues.
Support implementation of AI governance frameworks, approval gates, and monitoring processes.
Collaborate with policy, IT, legal, privacy, and business teams to provide clear, actionable guidance on AI projects.
Document and report findings, including risk assessments, dashboards, and governance committee materials.
Stay up to date with AI regulatory requirements, privacy laws, and ethical AI principles, ensuring projects align with best practice.
Assist in embedding responsible AI practices and frameworks.


Skills & Experience
Essential:

Hands-on experience in AI governance, ethics, and responsible AI frameworks.
Understanding of ethical AI principles: bias/fairness, & transparency.
Experience assessing AI projects for compliance, risk, and governance concerns.
Strong analytical skills and ability to review data sets, model outputs, or AI tools.
Experience with ServiceNow or similar governance/tracking tools.
Excellent communication skills to translate technical risks into clear advice for senior management.


Desirable / Nice-to-Have:

Background in government/public sector, consulting, finance, regulated industries, academia, or tech companies with AI governance exposure.
Knowledge of AI regulatory requirements, PIAs, or model risk frameworks.
Experience supporting governance committees, dashboards, and reporting frameworks.

"If AI governance and ethics excite you, we want to hear from you!"

Ad Text:
About the role

As the Intelligence Automation Specialist, you will design and implement system-supported workflows and intelligent automation that improve efficiency, consistency, and scalability. You will translate governed business processes into reliable, explainable automation using low-code, rule-based, and selective AI-assisted approaches—ensuring strong controls, transparency, and human oversight.

Key responsibilities

Analyse end-to-end processes and identify automation opportunities

Design and implement workflows using low-code and rule-based platforms (e.g. Power Platform)

Build logic for validation, approvals, task routing, notifications, and exception handling

Configure event-driven, agent-assisted, and RPA solutions where appropriate

Ensure automation aligns with governance, privacy, security, and SOPs

Maintain documentation, version control, and change management

Monitor, troubleshoot, and optimise automation performance

Collaborate with Business Analysts, system support, governance, and IT teams


About you

Essential

Qualification in IT, Computer Science, or equivalent practical experience

Strong experience delivering workflow automation or low-code solutions

Ability to translate business rules into executable logic

Experience with validation, approvals, routing, and exception handling

Experience working across multiple systems in regulated environments

Strong documentation and communication skills

Experience with Microsoft Power Platform (e.g. Power Automate) or similar tools

Desirable

RPA or intelligent automation experience

Exposure to AI-assisted decision support in governed environments

Experience in health, government, or compliance-heavy sectors


Why You’ll Love It Here

Boost Your Take-Home Pay: Access generous salary packaging options

Flexible Work, Real Balance: Hybrid working that supports life outside work

Parental Leave That Cares: 10 weeks of paid parental leave

Extra Leave for You: Leave loading and dedicated festive leave

Support When It Matters: 5 additional paid carers leave days

Wellbeing First: Free, confidential EAP support for you and your family

Values-Led Culture: Purpose-driven, people-focused and genuinely collaborative

Health & Wellness: Access annual health programs, vaccinations and wellbeing initiatives

Grow With Us: Ongoing learning, development and career progression opportunities
